    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application transforms the linear text guide into an interactive cheatsheet. It uses a sticky top navigation bar for quick jumps between the three core sections: Essentials, Workflow, and Troubleshooting. Each command is presented as an interactive card within a grid layout. This structure was chosen to make the information highly scannable and immediately useful, as users can copy commands directly to their clipboard. This is more user-friendly than a simple text document for a technical reference guide. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: Git commands and descriptions. Goal: Inform and provide a quick reference. Presentation Method: Interactive cards with styled code blocks and descriptions. Interaction: A 'Copy' button for each command that copies the command text to the user's clipboard, providing instant utility. Justification: This transforms passive information into an active tool, which is ideal for a developer cheatsheet. Library/Method: HTML/Tailwind for structure and styling, Vanilla JS for copy-to-clipboard functionality. No charts are needed as there is no quantitative data. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
